- content_for :title, 'Accessibility'

.container.full
  .row.align-items-stretch.full
    .col-md-5.bg-dark-2.text-light
      .heading.mt-3 Accessibility
      .p.mb-5
        Securium is committed to providing a website that is accessible to the widest possible audience,
        regardless of technology or ability.
      .p.mb-5
        We are actively working to increase the accessibility and usability of our website and in doing
        so adhere to many of the available standards and guidelines.
    .col-md-7.bg-light.py-5
      .p.mb-5
        This website endeavours to conform to level Double-A of the World Wide Web Consortium (W3C)
        #{ link_to 'Web Content Accessibility Guidelines 2.1', 'https://www.w3.org/TR/WCAG20/'}. These guidelines
        explain how to make web content more accessible for people with disabilities. Conformance with these guidelines
        will help make the web more user friendly for all people.
      .p.mb-5
        This site has been built using code compliant with W3C standards for HTML and CSS. The site displays
        correctly in current browsers and using standards compliant HTML/CSS code means any future browsers will also display it correctly.
      .p.mb-5
        Whilst Securium strives to adhere to the accepted guidelines and standards for accessibility and
        usability, it is not always possible to do so in all areas of the website.
      .p.mb-5
        We are continually seeking out solutions that will bring all areas of the site up to the same level of
        overall web accessibility. In the meantime should you experience any difficulty in accessing the
        Securium website, please donâ€™t hesitate to #{ link_to 'contact', '/contact_us'} us.
      .p.mb-5
        If you are experiencing difficulty viewing the site due to the colour scheme, please visit the
        - if user_signed_in?
          #{ link_to 'My Account', "/users/#{current_user.id}"} page where you will be able to switch to a High Contrast theme.
        - else
          My Account page once you are logged in where you will be able to switch to a High Contrast theme.
